course_title: Clinical Procedures in Primary Care Settings

sections.comments: IF course is FULL please contact School of Nursing Student Support Office (academic.support@nursing.ubc.ca)This course is prioritized for 1st Year MN-NP students.An overview of common office procedures used in primary care practice by a Nurse Practitioner (NP). Primary care diagnostic and treatment procedures such as x-ray interpretation, ECG interpretation, IUD insertion, suturing, shave and punch biopsies and administration of local anesthesia.
